    "recap_headline": "University of Massachusets Athletics",
    "recap_text": "HARTFORD, Conn. -\nUniversity of Massachusetts baseball dropped a 9-3 contest to Kent State on Saturday afternoon at Murren Family Field at DiBenedetto Stadium.\nUMass fell to 5-9 overall on the season and 1-7 in the Mid-American Conference, while Kent State improved to 17-4 overall and 7-1 in the league.\nGavin O'Brien\nand\nJack Beverly\nhad two hits each, which included a doble from Beverly.\nAnthony Tirado\nand\nVance Bonior\nboth registered a hit, as Bonior recorded his first double of the season.\nWill Briggs\nand Bonior tallied one RBI apiece, as Tirado,\nReece McCarthy\nand Beverly all scored a run.\nMassachusetts took an early 1-0 lead in the opening frame. Tirado led off the inning with a single down the left field line, before advancing to third on a passed ball.\nTy Fox\nthen walked. Fox was caught stealing second, as Tirado left third on the throw down by the Kent State catcher. Tirado slid into home and gave UMass its first run of the day.\nKent State scored one run on a sacrifice fly in the third to knot the game up at 1-1. The Golden Flashes tacked on eight runs in the top of the fifth to take a 9-1 lead.\nUMass added another run on an RBI double from Bonior to score \u00a0Beverly in the bottom of the fifth and make it a 9-2 contest.\nIn the sixth, the Minutemen put up a run to make it a 9-3 game. McCarthy crossed the plate on a sacrifice fly by Briggs.\nThe two teams remained scoreless through the final three innings as Kent State held on to the 9-3 win.\nAdam Merritt\n(0-2) had the loss for UMass, allowing six runs on two hits, walking four and striking out a career-best five in 4.2 innings of work.\nEaston Tumis (4-1) earned the win for Kent State, giving up two runs on four hits, a walk and striking out three in five complete innings.\nMassachusetts and Kent State set for a 12 p.m. contest to conclude the series on Sunday, March 22 at Murren Family Field at DiBenedetto Stadium in Hartford, Connecticut.",
    "watch_url": null
  },
